          "body": "*For I, the LORD, do not change* (3:6) is the theological anchor of the section: God's covenant fidelity is why Israel still exists despite their robbery of Him. The call *return to Me* (3:7) meets the cynical question *how shall we return?* — and God answers concretely: stop robbing Me in *tithes and offerings*. The indictment is sharp. Tithes (Leviticus 27:30; Deuteronomy 14:22-29) were not optional generosity but covenantal obligation — the support of Levites, sanctuary, and poor. Withholding them was theft from God Himself. Then comes the unique invitation: *test Me now in this* (3:10). Nowhere else in Scripture does God invite His people to test Him — and the test is specific: *bring the whole tithe* and watch Him *open the windows of heaven* and *rebuke the devourer*. The agricultural blessing language (rain through opened windows, locusts rebuked) is Deuteronomic covenant blessing (Deuteronomy 28:1-14). The promise is corporate and land-specific; it is not a NT prosperity formula. But the principle endures — covenant generosity is met by covenant faithfulness."
